cast_shell: gate UI-DevTools on the explicit switch only

cast_shell built with is_castos=true defaults BUILD_ENG. The default
BUILD_ENG path unconditionally starts the UI-DevTools server on port
9223. That collides with the page DevTools bind that the kiosk
launcher needs at 9223.

Gate UI-DevTools on the --enable-ui-devtools switch only so a user has
to opt in; otherwise the port stays free for page DevTools.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [kiosk-specific use case]

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>

--- a/chromecast/browser/cast_browser_main_parts.cc
+++ b/chromecast/browser/cast_browser_main_parts.cc
@@ -605,9 +605,9 @@
   // Start UI devtools if this is a dev device or explicitly enabled.
   // Note that this must happen before the window tree host is created by the
   // window manager.
-  auto build_type = CreateSysInfo()->GetBuildType();
-  if (CAST_IS_DEBUG_BUILD() || build_type == CastSysInfo::BUILD_ENG ||
-      ::ui_devtools::UiDevToolsServer::IsUiDevToolsEnabled(
+  // Gate purely on the explicit switch; UI-DevTools' default port 9223
+  // collides with our kiosk's page DevTools bind otherwise.
+  if (::ui_devtools::UiDevToolsServer::IsUiDevToolsEnabled(
           ::ui_devtools::switches::kEnableUiDevTools)) {
     // Starts the UI Devtools server for browser Aura UI
     ui_devtools_ =
